cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of detecting regions of interest in histopathological images, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of superpixels and parallelization, which are techniques commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of prediction strategies and reuse of information also suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
